  "body": "Hey Guys , \n\nWe have question regarding ECIES.  \nIt looks like  the KDF doesn't use \nHMAC-SHA256 at all, it just uses \nthe plain SHA256 hash. \n\nWe also see that:  HMAC is used but \nfor the messageTag and not for the KDF\nas expected by standard.\n\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/crypto/ecies/ecies.go#L232\n\nis it by design or a missed bug ? \n\n @obscuren  @fjl @subtly @devrandom\n\nThanks in advance\nRoman\n",
